# provision/userlayer.sums — sha256 of EVERY skeleton version ever shipped.
#
# This is what lets `hwe update` tell "untouched default" from "the user's
# file": a layer file whose hash appears here was never edited, so a newer
# shipped default may quietly replace it. A file matching NO line is the
# user's and is never rewritten (only `hwe update --reset-defaults` may,
# and it backs up first).
#
# APPEND-ONLY. When a skeleton changes, add the NEW hash — never remove the
# old one (installs in the field still carry the old bytes, and forgetting
# the old hash silently freezes their defaults). A test pins every current
# skeleton to this list; `just skel-sums` appends what is missing.
f64bb3d0f9a08a0d04d7b519684cd49926b281d1dd2a2fc494776381963c9b61  hypr.conf
f586be8b3a593c6fe09afe4ebb46c5fdae39621ab40048474daf15b80ae7a206  hyprsunset.conf
2720784e8643e05919ca89f0cb06e87065f6ba8f64a764ed015a78bb90b6f652  packages-aur.lst
baeba1540830b99c4cc9875882e94ca5d0318dacb65dfe1c9aa209c3810c7f4f  packages.lst
545dcef6feb5b2ad6e495129bf304d1c76cf99434b395859769277086491dd77  waybar.jsonc
